data.chText: 股市价格一直停滞不动，现在又在上涨了。
data.enText: Prices on the stock market, which have been static, are now rising again.

data.enText: My hair gets full of static when I brush it.

example: they will probably give you a lot of static about your editorial

tr: a crackling or hissing noise caused by electrical interference

example: the inertia of an object at rest

tr: concerned with or producing or caused by static electricity
example: an electrostatic generator produces high-voltage static electricity

value.def: Something that is static does not move or change.

example.ex: The number of young people obtaining qualifications has remained static or decreased...
example.tran: 获得资格证的年轻人数量一直维持不变或出现下降。

example.ex: Both your pictures are of static subjects.
example.tran: 你的两张照片拍的都是静止物体。

value.def: Static or static electricity is electricity which can be caused by things rubbing against each other and which collects on things such as your body or metal objects.
If there is static on the radio or television, you hear a series of loud noises which spoils the sound.
value.tran: (广播、电视里的)静电噪声，静电干扰
